{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 16:49:31.063560", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary\\n- Overall fabric control-plane appears healthy: all EBGP sessions across leaves, spines, and the super-spine are established and exchanging the expected /24 host routes.\\n- The main anomaly is endpoint pc_0_0 being down/unreachable. This causes ARP failure on leaf_router_0_0’s access interface and renders 10.0.0.2 unreachable. The rest of the fabric forwards correctly.\\n\\nControl-plane health (FRR/EBGP)\\n- leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200): 4 neighbors (spines 65100–65103) all Established; each neighbor advertising 7 prefixes. Local routes include 10.0.0.0/24 (connected) and 7 remote /24s via uplinks.\\n- leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201): 4 neighbors (spines 65100–65103) all Established; each neighbor advertising 7 prefixes. Local routes include 10.0.1.0/24 (connected) and 7 remote /24s via uplinks.\\n- spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100) and spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101): EBGP Established to super-spine (AS 65000) and to leaves (AS 65200–65203). Both spines have BGP routes for all leaf /24s.\\n- super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000): EBGP Established to spines. Has routes for all leaf /24s via spines.\\n\\nData-plane observations\\n- Inter-leaf L3 reachability:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 -> 10.0.1.1 and leaf_router_0_1 -> 10.0.0.1 succeed when sourced from their respective SVI addresses (10.0.0.1 and 10.0.1.1). This confirms correct end-to-end routing across the fabric.\\n  - Note: Unsourced/default pings between 10.0.0.1 and 10.0.1.1 initially failed due to using 172.16.x.x as source addresses. Infra /31s are not advertised end-to-end (by design), so replies to those sources fail. This is expected behavior and not a fabric fault.\\n- Host pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2/24):\\n  - Up and reachable. pc_0_1 -> 10.0.1.1 (its gateway) succeeds.\\n  - pc_0_1 -> 10.0.0.1 (remote leaf SVI) succeeds via the fabric, confirming cross-pod/service reachability to the remote leaf gateway.\\n- Host pc_0_0 (expected 10.0.0.2/24):\\n  - Host container is not running: attempts to execute commands on pc_0_0 fail with “container … is not running”.\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 ARP table for eth4 shows “10.0.0.2 INCOMPLETE”; pings from leaf_router_0_0 to 10.0.0.2 fail, confirming no ARP response on the access segment.\\n  - pc_0_1 -> 10.0.0.2 also fails (expected), as the endpoint is down.\\n\\nLocalization of fault\\n- Impacted segment: Access network 10.0.0.0/24 on leaf_router_0_0.\\n- Impacted device: Endpoint pc_0_0 (the only host on that segment).\\n- Fabric devices (leafs/spines/super-spine) show normal control-plane and data-plane behavior for routed prefixes; no anomalies detected in BGP adjacencies or routing tables.\\n\\nRoot cause\\n- Endpoint failure: pc_0_0 container is not running, causing ARP resolution to 10.0.0.2 to fail on leaf_router_0_0 and making the host unreachable.\\n- No evidence of routing or forwarding faults in the fabric. The initial inter-leaf ping failures without explicit source IP were due to expected design (infra /31s not globally routed), not a network issue.\\n\\nRelevant evidence\\n- pc_0_0: command execution errors indicate container not running.\\n- leaf_router_0_0 ARP: 10.0.0.2 INCOMPLETE; pings to 10.0.0.2 fail.\\n- leaf_router_0_1 ARP: 10.0.1.2 present (STALE but reachable); pings to 10.0.1.2 succeed.\\n- leaf_router_0_0 <-> leaf_router_0_1: pings between 10.0.0.1 and 10.0.1.1 succeed when sourced from SVI IPs.\\n- BGP summaries on all routers show Established sessions and expected prefixes learned/advertised.\\n\\nAssessment\\n- Fabric health: Normal.\\n- Abnormal behavior: Host pc_0_0 down; ARP and Layer-3 reachability to 10.0.0.2 fail as a consequence.\\n- Scope/impact: Traffic to/from 10.0.0.2 is impacted; other prefixes and inter-leaf routing are unaffected., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='b92c68a1-964a-4316-8691-1ebcec7f07fa'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
